TITLE: Defining Complex Multipart Form Data Request Body in YAML
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to define a detailed multipart/form-data request body with various types of data including primitive values, objects, binary data, and arrays with different default Content-Types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/oai/openapi-specification/blob/main/versions/3.0.0.md#2025-04-18_snippet_41

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
requestBody:
  content:
    multipart/form-data:
      schema:
        type: object
        properties:
          id:
            type: string
            format: uuid
          address:
            # default Content-Type for objects is `application/json`
            type: object
            properties: {}
          profileImage:
            # default Content-Type for string/binary is `application/octet-stream`
            type: string
            format: binary
          children:
            # default Content-Type for arrays is based on the `inner` type (text/plain here)
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
          addresses:
            # default Content-Type for arrays is based on the `inner` type (object shown, so `application/json` in this example)
            type: array
            items:
              type: '#/components/schemas/Address'
```

