TITLE: Defining an Operation Object in JSON
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to define an Operation Object in JSON format. It includes various fields such as tags, summary, operationId, consumes, produces, parameters, responses, and security requirements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/oai/openapi-specification/blob/main/versions/2.0.md#2025-04-18_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "tags": [
    "pet"
  ],
  "summary": "Updates a pet in the store with form data",
  "description": "",
  "operationId": "updatePetWithForm",
  "consumes": [
    "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
  ],
  "produces": [
    "application/json",
    "application/xml"
  ],
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "petId",
      "in": "path",
      "description": "ID of pet that needs to be updated",
      "required": true,
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "name": "name",
      "in": "formData",
      "description": "Updated name of the pet",
      "required": false,
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "name": "status",
      "in": "formData",
      "description": "Updated status of the pet",
      "required": false,
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "responses": {
    "200": {
      "description": "Pet updated."
    },
    "405": {
      "description": "Invalid input"
    }
  },
  "security": [
    {
      "petstore_auth": [
        "write:pets",
        "read:pets"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

