TITLE: Runtime Expression Syntax - OpenAPI Specification
DESCRIPTION: ABNF syntax definition for runtime expressions used in Link Objects and Callback Objects. Defines the grammar for accessing request and response data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/oai/openapi-specification/blob/main/versions/3.0.1.md#2025-04-18_snippet_64

LANGUAGE: abnf
CODE:
```
expression = ( "$url" | "$method" | "$statusCode" | "$request." source | "$response." source )
source = ( header-reference | query-reference | path-reference | body-reference ) 
header-reference = "header." token
query-reference = "query." name 
path-reference = "path." name
body-reference = "body" ["#" fragment]
fragment = a JSON Pointer [RFC 6901]
name = *( char )
char = as per RFC [7159]
token = as per RFC [7230]
```

