TITLE: Complex Schema Definition with Discriminator in OpenAPI 3.0 YAML
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates a more complex schema definition using allOf construct with a discriminator, showing how to avoid redundancy in schema definitions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/oai/openapi-specification/blob/main/versions/3.0.1.md#2025-04-18_snippet_77

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
components:
  schemas:
    Pet:
      type: object
      required:
      - pet_type
      properties:
        pet_type:
          type: string
      discriminator:
        propertyName: pet_type
        mapping:
          cachorro: Dog
    Cat:
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Pet'
      - type: object
        # all other properties specific to a `Cat`
        properties:
          name:
            type: string
    Dog:
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Pet'
      - type: object
        # all other properties specific to a `Dog`
        properties:
          bark:
            type: string
    Lizard:
      allOf:
      - $ref: '#/components/schemas/Pet'
      - type: object
        # all other properties specific to a `Lizard`
        properties:
          lovesRocks:
            type: boolean
```

